latestPosts.caption:
When you hit a milestone birthday, you naturally pause to take stock of the life you’ve lived — and the life still ahead.

So when my 22-year-old niece recently asked me what the best part of my life has been so far, I surprised myself by saying, “This part.”

And when she followed it up by asking for a piece of advice, I told her simply: “Live in the moment, cherish your family, and always carry an attitude of gratitude.”

Of course, I’m human — I do lose sight of these things at times. But moments like these are a gentle reminder to slow down, be present, and appreciate all the blessings I’m surrounded by.

So here’s to being right here, right now — and to this beautiful chapter.
Happy 50th to us @deeps_lalkaka 💫🥂
